reviewText: I accidentally clicked on this title - but being open-minded I decided to watch it to see if it was worth the view.  That was likely the worst and most wasted 10 minutes of television I can remember.  I stopped counting how many times the word "fashion" was used (with enumerable descriptors attached - that somehow was supposed to give clarity and meaning their references).  I'm sure if I watched it through fruition, "fashion" would have been used to describe how a "fashion director" relieves themselves.  It was genuinely used to describe pretty much anything - which means the word in fact actually has no meaning.Pathetic, devoid of any substance and demonstrates (without any ambiguity) just how out of touch the arrogant, narcissistic and self-absorbed "high-fashion" crowd and industry as a whole really are (yes, that's a judgmental statement - but it is clearly accurate).  And yes, I easily came to that conclusion in less than 10 minutes of viewing - and I'm sure you would as well.But hey - maybe that's your 'thing'.
summary: Accidentally selected, watched for as long as I could stand - Absolute garbage.
Title: N/A
